A woman in her late 30s was struck by lightning in Johannesburg yesterday, paramedics said.She was found sitting in a passage at the premises of a business, ER24 spokesperson Chitra Bodasing Harduth said in a statement.She sustained moderate injuries and was taken to a nearby hospital.ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring could not immediately respond with details of where exactly the incident had taken place.In January, a woman was killed by a lightning strike in the Mpumalanga Lowveld. In February, three churchgoers were killed and 38 injured when lightning struck a tree in a veld in KwaMachi, KwaZulu-Natal.http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/woman-survives-lightning-strike-in-johannesburg-20161209